currentrevenue_summary:
As of the latest reports:

### Quarterly Revenue
- **Latest Quarter**: Q4 of Fiscal Year 2025
- **Revenue**: $11.1 billion
- **Reporting Period**: Ended May 31, 2025
- **Year-on-Year Change**: Declined by 12% compared to the same quarter last year.

### Annual Revenue
- **Fiscal Year 2025 Revenue**: $46.309 billion
- **Year-on-Year Change**: Declined by 10% compared to Fiscal Year 2024.

These figures indicate a challenging year for Nike, with both quarterly and annual revenues showing declines. The quarterly results slightly exceeded analyst expectations, but the overall trend reflects ongoing difficulties in demand.
guidance_revenue_summary:
Nike (NKE) has provided the following revenue guidance and outlook:

1. **Latest Revenue Results**:
   - For Q4 2025, Nike reported revenues of **$11.1 billion**, which is a **12% decline** year-over-year but exceeded analyst expectations by 3.4%. The previous year's revenue for the same quarter was **$12.61 billion**.
   - For the full fiscal year 2025, Nike's revenue is projected to be down **10%**, totaling approximately **$44.71 billion** compared to **$49.32 billion** in the previous year.

2. **Forward-Looking Guidance**:
   - **Next Quarter (Q1 2026)**: Analysts expect revenue to be around **$10.74 billion**.
   - **Current Fiscal Year (FY 2026)**: The revenue forecast is approximately **$45.21 billion**.

3. **Earnings Per Share (EPS)**:
   - The consensus EPS estimate for the next quarter is **$0.32**, and for the current fiscal year, it is **$1.82**.

These figures reflect a cautious outlook as Nike navigates challenges in demand and market conditions. For further details, you can refer to the [Yahoo Finance article](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nike-nke-tops-q4-earnings-212502795.html) and the [SEC filing](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/320187/000032018725000034/nke-20250626.htm).

**Sources:**
- [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nike-nke-tops-q4-earnings-212502795.html)
- [SEC Filing](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/320187/000032018725000034/nke-20250626.htm)
gross_profit_summary:
As of the latest financial report for Nike, Inc. (NKE):

### Quarterly Figures (Q4 FY2025)
- **Revenue**: $11.1 billion
- **Gross Profit**: Not explicitly stated, but gross margin decreased by **440 basis points** to **40.3%**.
- **Earnings Per Share (EPS)**: $0.14, compared to $1.01 in the same quarter last year.

### Annual Figures (FY2025)
- **Total Revenue**: Approximately $45.21 billion (based on estimates for the fiscal year).
- **Gross Profit (TTM)**: $19.79 billion.

### Trends
- The revenue for Q4 FY2025 represents a **12% decline** year-over-year.
- The gross margin decrease is attributed to increased costs, including tariffs, which are expected to impact margins further in the upcoming quarters.
- Analysts forecast that gross margins may continue to decline by **350-425 basis points** in the current quarter.

### Reporting Period
- The figures are for the quarter ended **May 31, 2025**.

For more detailed insights, you can refer to the [Nike Q4 Earnings Report](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nike-inc-reports-fiscal-2025-201500808.html) and other financial analyses.

**Sources:**
- [Yahoo Finance](https://finance.yahoo.com/news/nike-inc-reports-fiscal-2025-201500808.html)
